<div class="wikitext clearfix">



	<h1 class="pagetitle"><strong><a title="refresh" accesskey="2" href="tiki-index.php?page=General+maintenance">General maintenance</a></strong></h1>

 


<h2 class="showhide_heading" id="General_maintenance">General maintenance</h2>
<br />
<ul><li><a title="Filters" href="tiki-index.php?page=Filters" class="wiki ">Filters</a>
</li><li><a title="02 sensor" href="tiki-index.php?page=02+sensor" class="wiki ">02 sensor</a>
</li><li><a title="Oil service" href="tiki-index.php?page=Oil+service" class="wiki ">Oil service</a>
</li><li><a title="Spark plugs" href="tiki-index.php?page=Spark+plugs" class="wiki ">Spark plugs</a>
</li><li><a title="V belts" href="tiki-index.php?page=V+belts" class="wiki ">V belts</a>
</li></ul>
<br />
The Bmw E34 maintenance consists of three groups (I created PDF files to help you tracking the maintenance you have done):<br />
 Oil service (every 7,500 miles or 6 months)<br />
 Inspection I (every 15,000 miles or 12 months)<br />
 Inspection II (every other 15,000 miles or 24 months)<br />
Additional service includes:<br />
<br />
Oxygen sensor replacement (every 60,000 miles or 100,000 miles for '95)<br />
Brake/clutch fluid replacement (every 2 years)<br />
Timing belt replacement (M20 every 60,000 miles - 100,000km or 4 years)<br />
Coolant replacement (every 2 years)<br />
A/C microfilter replacement ('90 on)<br />
V-belts (every four years)<br />
The E34 has a service interval computer to indicate when the maintenance is due, you might want to note the mileage on a service book instead....<br />
<br />
<h3 class="showhide_heading" id="Procedure">Procedure</h3>
Example of service maintenance with synthetic oil:<br />
<ul><li>7,500 miles - Oil service
</li><li>15,000 miles - Inspection I
</li><li>22,500 miles - Oil service
</li><li>30,000 miles - Inspection II
</li><li>37,500 miles - Oil service
</li><li>45,000 miles - Inspection I
</li></ul>
...<br />
<br />



